<SECOND>PM-Britain-Amnesty Chad,0195</SECOND>
<HEAD>Amnesty Protests Detention of Former Chadian Minister</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Amnesty International has protested to Chad over
the detention without trial of Moukhtar Bachar Moukhtar, the
secretary of state in the Ministry of Agriculture until shortly
before his arrest.
   The international human rights organization said it had received
reports that Moukhtar is seriously ill.
   Amnesty International expressed serious concern about the case in
a Jan. 9 report, a spokeswoman said Friday. She spoke on condition
of anonymity.
   ``We haven't heard anything since then and as far as we know he
is still seriously ill and in detention,'' the spokeswoman said.
   Amnesty International said that since Chadian leader Hissene
Habre came to power in 1982, no political prisoners have been
brought to trial or had their cases referred to judicial
authorities. Instead, prisoners have been kept in secret detention
where many reportedly have died.
   Moukhtar, who formerly had been director-general of the
department of national education, was a member f the ruling party
and not known to have opposed the government.
   Amnesty International said that according to some reports he was
suspected of having criticized Habre.
