<DATELINE>FORT WAYNE, Ind. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A fire in the cockpit of an F-4E Indiana
Air National Guard jet forced the navigator to land the plane when
the pilot lost consciousness, officials said. The pilot later died.
   Both crewmen ejected from the aircraft as it taxied on the runway
at Baer Field on Friday, said Lt. Kathleen Rzepka of the Indiana
Guard.
   1st Lt. David E. Kruse, 26, of Fort Wayne, died at Lutheran
Hospital, Rzepka said. The cause of death was not available.
   Maj. Wilburt J. Elliott, 39, of South Bend, the weapons system
officer on the jet, made the emergency landing. He was listed in
good condition, Rzepka said.
   The F-4 belongs to the Guard's 122 Tactical Fighter Wing.
   The cause of the fire, which apparently was out when the plane
landed, was under investigation.
