<HEAD>Small Fire Breaks Out on Oil Platform, No Injuries</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A small fire broke out on an oil platform in the
North Sea, but it was extinguished quickly and caused no injuries,
officials said.
   The fire flared late Friday on a platform owned by Texaco Inc.,
said a company spokesman. He said a crewman on the rig put it out.
   The 180 workers on the platform 118 miles off the east coast of
Scotland were sent to lifeboat stations but were not evacuated, said
the spokesman, speaking anonymously in keeping with British custom.
   He said the platform was not damaged and the cause of the blaze
was being investigated.
   The platform is in the Tartan field, near the Piper Alpha oil
platform, which was destroyed by fiery explosions that killed 167
men in July.
