<SECOND>AM-Plane Crash,0173</SECOND>
<HEAD>Small Plane Rips Off Car Roof, Killing Passenger Inside</HEAD>
<DATELINE>YARMOUTH, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A small plane trying to make an emergency
landing at an airport Saturday sheared off the roof of a car
traveling on a nearby highway, killing a woman inside, police said.
   Doris L. Chase, 63, of South Yarmouth, died of massive head
trauma when the Piper Cherokee plane peeled off the roof of the car
in which she was a passenger, said state Trooper William Cisternelli.
   Her husband, who was driving, and the plane's three passengers
were taken to Cape Cod Hospital, where they were treated for minor
injuries and released, officials said.
   The pilot, Robert A. Feversanger, 27, tried to bring the plane
down on a highway near the airport when his airplane's throttle
apparently jammed, said state Trooper Robert Knott. The plane
crashed about 250 yards from the Barnstable Muncipal Airport, he
said.
   Police said Saturday evening the incident was still under
investigation and there were no charges pending against Feversanger.
