<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Worries about rising inflation and interest rates
touched off the biggest stock selloff of the year, depressed bond
prices and boosted the dollar's value against foreign currencies.
   The Dow Jones industrial average tumbled 36.97 points to 2,286.07
on Friday, the biggest drop in the key market indicator since Nov.
16.
   An accompanying decline in the bond market was more modest, but
extended the losses bonds suffered Thursday in a selloff that was
the sharpest in three months for the credit markets.
   Meanwhile, the dollar rallied on the prospect that the Federal
Reserve Board might tighten its monetary policy _ pushing interest
rates even higher _ in an effort to choke off inflation.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>KENNEBUNKPORT, Maine (AP) </DATELINE>
